     <div class="l_upper_section">
      <img alt="som" height="270" src="/images/somrb5.jpg" width="700"/>
      <h3>
       UCR Health Compliance: Learning to Make the Right Choices
      </h3>
      <p>
       The compliance program of the UCR School of Medicine and UCR Health is all about making the right choices and demonstrating to both internal and external stakeholders the organization's continued commitment to making proper and ethical decisions.
      </p>
      <p>
       This site will provide you with information regarding the compliance program, the code of conduct and answers to common questions and guidance documents; including information on industry relations, privacy &amp; security and research.
      </p>
     </div>
     <h4 class="sun-burst">
      About the Compliance Program
     </h4>
     <p>
      The Compliance Program ensures that UCR Health serves as a role model for good corporate citizenship in health care in core teaching, research, patient care, and public service missions.
     </p>
     <ul>
      <li>
       <a href="/program_description/index.html">
        Learn more about the UCR Health Compliance Program
       </a>
      </li>
     </ul>
     <h4 class="sun-burst">
      About the Code of Conduct
     </h4>
     <p>
      The Code of Conduct is an integral part of this compliance program and reflects the values of the organization. The ability of the medical school and UCR Health to advance its mission depends upon the capability of all employees to support one another in upholding these values.
     </p>
     <ul>
      <li>
       <a href="/code_of_conduct/index.html">
        Learn more about the Code of Conduct
        <br/>
       </a>
      </li>
     </ul>
     <p>
     </p>
     <div class="nota-bene">
      <h4>
       Making a Report &amp; Contacting the Health Compliance Office
      </h4>
      The staff of the UC Riverside Health Compliance Office is available to respond to any question that you might have. If we don't have the answer, we'll try to find someone who does.
      <ul>
       <li>
        <a href="/contact_us/index.html">
         Learn how to contact Chief Compliance Officer Paul Hackman
        </a>
       </li>
       <li>
        <a class="external" href="https://secure.ethicspoint.com/domain/media/en/gui/23531/index.html">
         Submit a confidential report  through the University of California's Hotline website.
        </a>
       </li>
      </ul>
     </div>
    </div>
